  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is a medico-economic evaluation to estimate a cost differential between
      three modalities of Intensity-Modulated Radiation Therapy for cancers of the prostate, cervix
      and anal canal with pelvic lymph node irradiation : treatment with helical Tomotherapy and
      dynamic arc therapy using two different technologies: RapidArc or VMAT.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
